<SLUG> BC-BKC-UCLANOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
UCLA'S GADZURIC WAS TALL MAN OUT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JON WILNER  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ It wasn't center Dan Gadzuric's four turnovers
that limited him to 17 minutes Saturday against Arizona State, UCLA
coach Steve Lavin said. It was Gadzuric's size.
</P>
<P>
   He was too big.
</P>
<P>
   ``I told Dan he didn't do anything wrong, it was just the
matchups,'' Lavin said.
</P>
<P>
   To counter ASU's small but speedy lineup, the Bruins removed
Gadzuric, moved forward Jerome Moiso to center and inserted
athletic forward Matt Barnes.
</P>
<P>
   The quintet of Moiso, Barnes, Jason Kapono, Ray Young and Earl
Watson played extensively, including the final eight minutes of
UCLA's 83-77 victory. It accounted for 76 points, 27 rebounds and
held ASU to 33.3 percent shooting in the second half.
</P>
<P>
   ``The smaller lineup was a more difficult matchup for them,''
Lavin said. ``Last year we went small to win a lot of games.''
</P>
<P>
   The Bruins might use the lineup this week at the Oregon schools,
which often align four perimeter players around one big man.
</P>
<P>
   ``(The small lineup) is good for us because all the guys can do
so many things,'' Kapono said. ``Jerome plays (center) but he's
really a (forward), Matt plays (power forward) but he's really a
(small forward). It's a skilled, versatile, quick team.''
</P>
<P>
   Injury update: Junior guard Rico Hines believes he broke his
right big toe Saturday and will have X-rays today.
</P>
<P>
   ``I broke it last year, and I know how it feels,'' Hines said.
``I heard it snap.''
</P>
<P>
   Hines started Saturday in place of Young for the third
consecutive game. The injury occurred on UCLA's second possession,
when he jammed his toe into ASU guard Eddie House's foot. Hines
departed a few seconds later and did not return.
</P>
<P>
   UCLA called the injury a sprain, pending results of the X-rays.
But if Hines is right and his toe is broken, watch for Young to
return to the starting lineup.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
