funding alone has ballooned from $1 million in 1997 to $454 million
this year, represents nothing less than a re-imagining of the
school day for the first time in generations, as educators and
policymakers seek to respond to the realities of working families
and what may be missing from the classroom. (Suzanne DeChillo/The
