State of the Union speech. Edwards is the first African-American
speechwriter to work in the White House. ``I hope I'm not the last.
But once you get in there and once you are inundated by the pace
and demands of the job, historic significances take a back seat to
immediate actions.'' (Shana Raab/The New York Times)
